{
  "stem": "4361.5",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "By this time, before I was part of this Brzezinka commando, hunger was endemic.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "By this time, and I'm speaking for myself, hunger was the most powerful force that kept me alive, because hunger made me scrounge for a potato peel, if you will.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "Hunger also obliterated any insight into what was happening.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "I couldn't think of anything else but hunger.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And maybe that was why when I finally knew that that poor old timer was telling me the truth when she was pointing to the chimneys, I was hungry.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And it was like an earthquake, but the aftershock of the earthquake that came much later was the more terrible, precisely because there was no morning, when morning should have been the proper time for it.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And while I was in this Brzezinka, I found-- I find-- I found food in some of the valises, and I used to smuggle them in.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "For instance, toothpaste was a great contraband, because there was black market.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "You would exchange a diamond for a piece of bread.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And I would line my sleeves with toothpaste, and give it to some of the girls with whom I shared the bunk.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And it was very painful, because I opened valises, and I found children's clothing, and I found pictures, and I found the whole background of thousands and thousands of Hungarian Jews, because we were the first transport, as I learned much later.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "My town and my transport was the first one.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "After about four or eight weeks, I was put in another commando called the [NON-ENGLISH] which was a factory on the premises somewhere in Lager B.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We walked.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "How did we walk?",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
